# LocalMoney Solana - Development Workflow

## Project Architecture
LocalMoney is a P2P trading platform with 5 interconnected Solana programs:

### Core Programs
- **[Hub](mdc:programs/hub/)**: Central coordination and configuration
- **[Offer](mdc:programs/offer/)**: Buy/sell offer management  
- **[Trade](mdc:programs/trade/)**: Escrow and trade lifecycle
- **[Price](mdc:programs/price/)**: Currency pricing oracle
- **[Profile](mdc:programs/profile/)**: User profile management

## Development Setup

### Prerequisites
- Rust 1.70+
- Solana CLI 1.16+
- Anchor CLI 0.31.1
- Node.js 16+ with Yarn

### Initial Setup
```bash
# Install dependencies
yarn install

# Build all programs
anchor build

# Generate TypeScript types
anchor build && anchor deploy
```

## Daily Development Workflow

### 1. Start Development Session
```bash
# Start local validator (in separate terminal)
anchor run start-local

# Verify cluster is localnet
solana config get
```

### 2. Make Changes
- Edit program code in `programs/{program_name}/src/`
- Update tests in `tests/`
- Modify IDL interfaces as needed

### 3. Build and Test
```bash
# Build changes
anchor build

# Deploy to localnet
anchor deploy

# Run tests
anchor run local-test
```

### 4. Debug Issues
```bash
# Check program logs
solana logs

# Get program account info
solana account {program_id}

# Airdrop SOL if needed
solana airdrop 10
```

## Code Organization

### Program Structure
Each program follows Anchor conventions:
```
programs/{program_name}/
├── src/
│   ├── lib.rs           # Main program entry
│   ├── instructions/    # Instruction handlers
│   ├── state/          # Account structures
│   ├── errors.rs       # Custom error types
│   └── constants.rs    # Program constants
├── Cargo.toml
└── Xargo.toml
```

### Testing Structure
```
tests/
├── {program_name}.ts   # Program-specific tests
├── utils/              # Test utilities
└── fixtures/           # Test data
```

## Cross-Program Communication
Programs interact via Cross-Program Invocation (CPI):
- Hub -> All other programs (configuration)
- Offer -> Trade (trade initiation)
- Trade -> Price (pricing data)
- Trade -> Profile (user verification)

## Best Practices

### Account Management
- Use PDAs for program-owned accounts
- Implement proper account constraints
- Validate account relationships
- Use `#[account(init)]` for new accounts
- Use `#[account(mut)]` for modifications

### Error Handling
- Define custom error enums
- Use descriptive error messages
- Implement proper error propagation
- Log errors for debugging

### Security
- Validate all inputs
- Check account ownership
- Implement proper authorization
- Use signer constraints where needed
- Validate cross-program calls

### Performance
- Minimize compute units usage
- Optimize account layouts
- Use efficient serialization
- Batch related operations

## Common Commands

### Development
```bash
# Full rebuild
anchor build

# Deploy specific program
anchor deploy --program-name {program_name}

# Run specific test file
anchor test tests/{program_name}.ts --skip-local-validator

# Clean build artifacts (use sparingly)
anchor clean
```

### Debugging
```bash
# Show program logs in real-time
solana logs | grep {program_id}

# Get account data
anchor account {account_type} {account_address}

# Decode transaction
solana confirm {transaction_signature} --verbose
```

## Integration Testing
Tests should cover:
1. Individual program functionality
2. Cross-program interactions
3. Error conditions
4. Edge cases
5. State transitions

